The paper discusses unsupervised learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on learning to predict without paired input-output training data, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science. The paper proposes an objective function that aims to make the predicted outputs fit well the structure of the output while preserving the correlation between the input and the predicted output. This suggests that the paper could be relevant to several sub-categories of arXiv CS, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as they are the most general and cover a wide range of topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The other categories are also relevant, as they deal with specific aspects of the problem, such as computer vision and natural language processing.
